          Title I of the State Department Basic
			 Authorities Act of 1956 (22 U.S.C. 2651a et seq.) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following:

subparagraph.text:
an even broader
				area defined as Arctic by temperature that includes the Bering Sea and Aleutian
				Islands;

is known to the
				indigenous population as Inuvikput, or the place where we
				live;

paragraph.text:
since 1959,
				temperatures in the Arctic region of the United States have warmed by 3 to 4
				degrees Celsius, a rate of increase more than twice the global average;
